A 21-year-old woman from Sydney, who was sentenced to 15 days in prison in Phuket for falsely claiming to have been raped by a taxi driver, has filed an appeal against the verdict and was released on bail.
Stevie Rochelle Bamford was initially found guilty by a provincial court in Phuket on June 15 after she told Thai police that a local taxi driver raped her in the morning hours on Sunday, June 10, while two other men arrested her.
Later, however, the footage of a video camera showed that she had safely reached her hotel after being separated from her Australian friend.
Police in Phuket interrogated Bamford for two days until she confessed to having come up with the story.
Until the trial, she was in police custody.
