Tunks told the Sunday Telegraph in Sydney that the entire family was "extremely concerned" about his daughter's well-being and wanted her back in Australia.
"Of course we are very worried, but we hope she's back home as soon as possible," Tunks said.
Bamford has appealed against the judgment and is against a bail of 50,000 baht on free foot.
Australian reports showed that she is on vacation in the resort of Krabi in southern Thailand in the meantime.
